    <div class="tg-hero__inner">
      <span class="tg-hero__type">Study Guide · 13 Chapters</span>
      <h1 class="tg-hero__title">Hebrews: The Better Covenant</h1>
      <p class="tg-hero__intro">
        The book of Hebrews makes the most sustained, OT-saturated argument in the New Testament:
        Jesus is the fulfilment and surpassing of everything God did in the old covenant — as
        prophet, priest, king, sacrifice, and covenant mediator. This guide works chapter by
        chapter, returning to every major Old Testament passage in its original context so the
        writer's case lands with its full cumulative force.
      </p>
      <blockquote class="tg-hero__key-verse">
        <p>Long ago, at many times and in many ways, God spoke to our fathers by the prophets,
           but in these last days he has spoken to us by his Son.</p>
        <cite><a class="ref" data-ref="Hebrews 1:1-2">Hebrews 1:1–2</a></cite>
      </blockquote>
    </div>
